The paper deals with zero-shot learning in convolutional neural networks for image classification tasks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The approach also involves incorporating domain knowledge through natural language captions and attributes, which falls under natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions providing textual explanations for the predictions made by the classifiers, which could involve information retrieval (cs.IR).
